  "body": "**Fix status:**\r\n- [x] fixed in master in https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/pull/61284, will be in 1.10.0\r\n- [x] fixed in release-1.9 branch in https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/pull/61308, will be in 1.9.7\r\n- [x] fixed in release-1.8 branch in https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/pull/61309, will be in 1.8.11\r\n- [x] fixed in release-1.7 branch in https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/pull/61310, will be in 1.7.16\r\n\r\nSubpaths of volumes with fsGroup may be mounted into a container without SGID bit on themselves:\r\n\r\n```sh\r\n$ kubectl create -f - <<EOF                                                                                                                kind: Pod\r\napiVersion: v1\r\nmetadata: { name: \"subpath\" }\r\nspec:\r\n  volumes:\r\n    - { name: \"direct\",  emptyDir: {}}\r\n    - { name: \"subpath\", emptyDir: {}}\r\n  securityContext:\r\n    fsGroup: 100\r\n    runAsUser: 35\r\n  containers:\r\n    - image: aosqe/hello-openshift\r\n      name: show\r\n      volumeMounts:\r\n        - name: \"direct\"\r\n          mountPath: \"/mnt/direct\"\r\n        - name: \"subpath\"\r\n          mountPath: \"/mnt/subpath\"\r\n          subPath: \"a\"\r\nEOF\r\n\r\n$ kubectl exec -ti subpath -- ls /mnt -la\r\ndrwxrwsrwx    2 root     users            6 Mar 16 15:13 direct\r\ndrwxrwxrwx    2 root     users            6 Mar 16 15:13 subpath\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe mode of `subpath` should be `drwxrwsrwx` instead of `drwxrwxrwx`.\r\n\r\nReason for this is `fchmod` at https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/blob/5110db5087513801fc5946abcbd73c44e692b2c8/pkg/util/mount/mount_linux.go#L1035:\r\n\r\n```go\r\n\tif err = syscall.Fchmod(parentFD, uint32(perm)&uint32(os.ModePerm)); err != nil {\r\n\t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"chmod %q failed: %s\", currentPath, err)\r\n\t}\r\n```\r\n\r\n1. it should not filter out sgid/suid/sticky flags with `&os.ModePerm`\r\n2. `Fchmod()` int32 argument expects suid/sgid/sticky flags on different bits than `os.FileMode`.\r\n\r\n\r\n/kind bug\r\n/sig storage\r\n@liggitt ",
